<PageTitle>Section 3: Functions and Responsibilities</PageTitle>

<div class="discipline-content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h1>Section 3: Functions and Responsibilities</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">DepEd School Discipline Rules of Procedure</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
        <div class="section-card">
            <h2>3.1 Primary Functions</h2>
            <p>The School Discipline Committee shall perform the following primary functions:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Investigation and Assessment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Conduct thorough investigation of disciplinary cases</li>
                    <li>Gather evidence and testimonies from all parties involved</li>
                    <li>Assess the severity and nature of violations</li>
                    <li>Determine appropriate disciplinary measures</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Decision Making</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Deliberate on disciplinary cases objectively</li>
                    <li>Ensure due process in all proceedings</li>
                    <li>Make recommendations to the school principal</li>
                    <li>Monitor implementation of disciplinary actions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>3.2 Specific Responsibilities</h2>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Case Management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Receive and document all disciplinary reports</li>
                    <li>Maintain confidentiality of all case proceedings</li>
                    <li>Ensure timely resolution of cases</li>
                    <li>Keep accurate records of all decisions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Student Welfare</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Protect the rights of students during proceedings</li>
                    <li>Ensure age-appropriate disciplinary measures</li>
                    <li>Coordinate with guidance counselors for student support</li>
                    <li>Monitor student progress after disciplinary action</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>3.3 Procedural Responsibilities</h2>
            <p>The committee shall ensure compliance with the following procedures:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Due Process Requirements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Notify students and parents of charges</li>
                    <li>Provide opportunity for defense and explanation</li>
                    <li>Allow presentation of evidence and witnesses</li>
                    <li>Ensure impartial and fair proceedings</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Documentation Requirements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Maintain detailed case files</li>
                    <li>Record all proceedings and decisions</li>
                    <li>Prepare written reports for all cases</li>
                    <li>Ensure proper filing and archiving of records</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>3.4 Communication Responsibilities</h2>
            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Internal Communication</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Coordinate with teachers and staff</li>
                    <li>Inform school administration of decisions</li>
                    <li>Update relevant personnel on case status</li>
                    <li>Maintain confidentiality within the school</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>External Communication</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Communicate with parents and guardians</li>
                    <li>Coordinate with external agencies when necessary</li>
                    <li>Report serious cases to appropriate authorities</li>
                    <li>Maintain professional relationships with stakeholders</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>3.5 Monitoring and Evaluation</h2>
            <p>The committee shall continuously monitor and evaluate:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Effectiveness of disciplinary measures</li>
                <li>Student behavior improvement</li>
                <li>Compliance with school policies</li>
                <li>Overall school discipline climate</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Annual Review</h3>
                <p>The committee shall conduct an annual review of:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Disciplinary cases handled during the year</li>
                    <li>Effectiveness of implemented measures</li>
                    <li>Recommendations for policy improvements</li>
                    <li>Training needs for committee members</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

